heaviest_rainfall.status: Ranked 7th for total rainfall, today's storm had precipitation totalling 22.48mm, falling at 8.3mm per hour at times during the 28.2 hour long storm.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 8th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 28.2 hours; it delivered 22.48mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The record duration for continuous rain was set on 09 November 2025, the storm lasted 144.8 hours with a total precipitation of 47.89mm and it reached 24.6mm per hour at times.
